<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN yes? **Zowie**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>b. Give it a minimum hit like flying kick was given, so we don't have the possibility of hitting for 8, 8, and 20.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>&nbsp;</SPAN></P>
<OL type=1 start=4 **Zowie**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: 0pt; l0><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>(Ability Resists) </SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>Resists on all 3 of our abilities (snare/stun/de-aggro) are way too high, they are currently resisted around 70% of the time.</SPAN></LI></OL>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Done</FONT></SPAN></P>
<OL type=1 start=5 **Zowie**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: 0pt; l0><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>(Tainted Axe of Hatred) </SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>Tainted Axe of Hatred.<SPAN yes? **Zowie**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Needs to be stackable and not Lore.<SPAN yes? **Zowie**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>In addition I think people would really like to see other dropped axe tomes which give axes with stats on them.<SPAN yes? **Zowie**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Tainted axe of hatred has 200 hps, there needs to be lesser tomes with lesser stats dropping at different places in EverQuest.</SPAN></LI></OL>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently on test server</FONT></SPAN></P>
<OL type=1 start=6 **Zowie**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: 0pt; l0><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>(Innate critical and crippling hits)</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>.<SPAN yes? **Zowie**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>Cleaving anger is broken because we don't have an innate chance at crippling blows, and we should.</SPAN></LI></OL>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;><FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></SPAN></P>
<OL type=1 start=7 **Zowie**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: 0pt; l0><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN yes? **Zowie**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp;</SPAN>(Throwing) </SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:>Throwing --- It is said that berserkers were supposed to be unmatched with throwing. And berserkers were supposed to be some great offensive class.<SPAN yes? **Zowie**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>They hardly do any dmg with throwing their axes. Speaking of which, axes NEED to have stats. Small stats for the lower level ones, and gradually become greater the higher level the axe. This is needed to make up for sacrificing our range slot for a summoned axe. SO it would be nice to have better stats as you get your higher level axes. </SPAN></LI></OL>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt? 0in **Zowie**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;>Currently being evaluated however; </SPAN><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: mso-bidi-font-family: Verdana; Arial? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;>throwing is intended to be a viable option for damage, but not equal dps to melee.&nbsp; The summoned ones can get some stat modifiers, but they can't really be expected to have equal stats to a dropped item of that level range.</SPAN></FONT><SPAN FONT-FAMILY: Verdana? **Zowie**?COLOR: red;></SPAN></P>
