			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=berserkerbalance&message.id=3284#M3284">22</a> of 27
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 2781 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><SPAN Verdana? **Zowie**?FONT-FAMILY:><SPAN>&nbsp;
<OL><SPAN><SPAN></OL>
<P><STRONG>1. Improve Melee performance, especially in the low and mid levels. <FONT color=#ff0000>This will most likely be considered as part of part #2 of the class Re-Envision process.</FONT></STRONG><BR></P>
<UL>
<LI>The community feels that there is a need for a review of the damage output a typical mid and low level Berserker is capable off. The only damage tool available at that range is Frenzy, which isn’t that much of an impact to truly define Berserkers as a true DPS class. Suggestions for improvements:<BR><BR>
<LI>Extend the Volley line for the mid and low levels. One Volley skill every 10 levels (1 for every other Axe Summon skill we get) seems appropriate.<BR><BR>
<LI>Addition of more low/mid level burst damage discs on different timers. The high end Berserkers start to shine with their ability to chain multiple DPS disciplines after each other, however until level level 65 all damage-oriented disciplines are on the same timer. The addition of lower level version of our Cleaving Anger and Vengeful Flurry disciplines as well as some lower level disciplines on the ‘old world’ discipline timers would be a great addition for these levels, and would great a more unified role for the Berserker across his lifetime.<BR></LI></UL>
<P><BR><B>2.Reevaluate the Endurance Cost of our Abilities. – <FONT color=#ff0000>This is being considered as part of round #1 of the class Re-Envision process.</FONT></B><BR></P>
<UL>
<LI>The cost of some of the abilities (especially the 3rd rank and above) as well as all Warcries seem to be a bit over the top.<BR></LI></UL>
<P><B>3. Itemization <FONT color=#ff0000>This is still in progress</FONT></B><BR></P>
<UL>
<LI>There is a definite lack of Berserker only items, or ‘Berserker preferred’ items. For example there is only 1 Berserker only weapon besides the Epic weapons less than a handful of items with a Frenzy Damage modifier and equally few items with a throwing focus.<BR><BR>
<LI>In addition to the above the selection of available throwing weapons is very limited. The only choices besides our normal summoned axes are the Tainted Axe of Hatred and Ton Po’s Mystical Pouch / Shuriken of Eternity, and even these are no real alternative to current high end loot, so most Berserkers either wear inferior items in their range slot of leave their Axes at home and use a normal range item.<BR><BR>
<LI>Apart from the lack of weaponry Berserkers have a distinct disadvantage in their stats since they can only wield 2Her weapons, which usually score at around 120% of the stats of comparable 1H weapons. In addition to the 80% we lose from the other weapon slot, we also lose an augmentation slot. In addition to the above mentioned lack of throwing weapons with good stats, we also lose another augmentation slot if we engage in ranged combat, because unlike bows our throwing weapons can’t really be augemented.<BR>Overall a lot of lost stats and we don’t even have the option to switch to 1Her combos or Bows if we wanted to.<BR>Solutions could be innate stat bonuses on the Primary weapon slot similar to how the Recommended level system takes stats away, or special (crafted/quested) Berserker only augmentations with a new slot added to all 2Hers.<BR></LI></UL>
<P><BR><B>4. War Cry Improvements / Raid utility.<FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed</FONT></B><BR>The community hopes that War Cries could be reviewed/revamped as they are the only unique ability and utility a Berserker can offer to a group or raid. The current form however does not bring enough power to the table to put the Berserkers class on the wish list of a group or raid leader. The limited impact, versatility and availability of the skill all factor into this. The community feedback and suggestions on this topic are far too lengthy and extensive to list them here, so I will only list a few short ideas.<BR></P>
<UL>
<LI>“Is it in yet?” - The bonus from War Cries is just to small considering the long reuse time and the fact that the typical group usually won’t have more than 2 – 3 melee characters in it. In raids special arrangements can be made but even then the casting range will more often than not cause one or two members to miss the effect.<BR><BR>
<LI>It’s too One-dimensional - We only have one type of War Cry, which makes it a “no brains” skill: As soon as the raid leader yells ‘Burn!!!’ or the group pulls a named mob we push the button and hope that someone notices. If we had different types of War Cries, i.e. one that boosts offensive powers while another one boosts the defensive abilities, we’d have to evaluate the situation and chose an appropriate tactic. Note: We do not anticipate getting a defensive type disc for Berserkers that would allow us to close in on the tanking skills of Plate classes. We are mainly looking for group/raid utility and would therefore be very happy about skills that only affect the group and not the Berserker.<BR><BR>
<LI>All for one and one for all - AE War Cries are still a big item on our wish list. If you don’t want powerful group disciplines to be AE’d then please create a special AE line for raids that is tuned appropriately. If you fear that AE War Cries would lessen the desire for multiple Berserkers on a raid, make the AE line shorter duration or add offensive/defensive War Cries (see above).<BR><BR>
<LI>We didn't recieve a new Warcry since Gates of Discord.<BR></LI></UL>
<P><BR><B>5. Throwing - <FONT color=#ff0000>Some improvements are being considered as part of round #1 of the class Re-Envision process.</FONT></B><BR>Throwing has a few problems that need to be addressed:<BR></P>
<UL>
<LI>The lack of good throwing weapons and the disadvantage of throwing weapons vs. a bow (see above).<BR>It would be absolutely great if the throwing skill could be reworked to work more closely to how Archery works. A bow like item in the range slot, i.e. a throwing glove or throwing satchel, that isn’t thrown away but rather enhances the range, damage and delay of the ammo (the actual axes, shurikens, knives, stones, etc). These bow-equivalents could be seeded across existing group, raid and crafting content and could be shared with Monks, Rogues, Beastlords, etc.<BR><BR>
<LI>The cost of summoned axes / lack of an endless quiver type AA make our throwing a heavy burden on our purses. It’s especially a bummer for those of us that wish to kite as a form of soloing. Please do the right thing and remove the cost for the components and/or give us an Endless Quiver AA. It’s a really inappropriate money sink, which also scares off new players from trying this class.<BR><BR>
<LI>Another problem with the current throwing weapons is the range of our throwing axes. The best one is currently 175 which is not enough to 'dodge' from AEs in raid encounters. Therefore, throwing isn't even a viable alternative to melee combat in those situations. Please extend it beyond 200 - any lvl 55+ bow has a range of 175 and can be easily extended beyond 200 with cheap arrows (even mage summoned arrows)<BR></LI></UL>
<P><BR><B>6. Combat Abilities - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being discussed<BR></FONT></B></P>
<UL>
<LI>Our Jolt line is on the same timer as our ‘offensive’ / agro-creating skills. The problem with this is that we very rarely grab agro from melee damage alone. In normal circumstances it only happens right after we used a stun, snare or volley attack and then our Jolt line is unavailable for 12 seconds.<BR><BR>
<LI>Snares: This ability line scales very poorly as the only difference from upgrading is the resist adjust field, which does not seem to make that much of a difference. The price for that upgrade is a great increase in endurance cost as well as monetary component cost (see #6 Throwing). We would appreciate if the duration and the Snare percentage would scale up with each rank as well. Right now they are all 55% snare with a 1 minute duration. I would suggest a 35%, 1minute, 45%, 2minute, 55% 3minute, 65% 4minute progression.<BR><BR>
<LI>Stuns: There is a gap in the stun progression in the mid 50s. The level 40 stun skill can stun NPCs up to level 55 while the next upgrade to the Stun line is available at level 60. Most NPCs in the lower planes where a typical mid 50s player would hunt are above level 55 and therefore immune to this stun.<BR>Another smaller gap appears between in the 65ish – 68 range as the level 60 stun works on NPCs up to level 65 and the next stun upgrade occurs at level 68; although this gap isn’t as dramatic as the previous one as most exp spots for that level range feature numerous NPCs of level 65 or below.<BR>I don’t really have an easy solution for this problem other than reviewing all the stun and adding more ranks to make the progression smoother, always allowing the Berserker to stun NPCs at least a few levels above him.<BR>For the high ends this problem returns again as the highest level stun works on NPCs up to level 70, which isn’t sufficient to work in places like Riftseekers or the Nest, therefore many have asked for a new stun or a stun AA that raises the level up to 72/73ish</LI></UL>
<P><BR><B>7. Endurance Regeneration - <FONT color=#ff0000>Currently being evaluated</FONT></B><BR></P>
<UL>
<LI>The innate endurance regeneration rate does not improve between level 65 and 70, while all combat abilities have become more expensive. 
<LI>We would very much like to see endurance regeneration items and/or spells to be added to the game. 
<LI>The slow rate of endurance regeneration becomes especially noticeable after resurrections or raid ‘burn’ situations. In the high end it can take 20 minutes or longer of pure idle time to recover from 0 endurance to full. Some ‘resting’ skill that allows us to regenerate endurance faster but adds some negatives to avoid abuse, i.e. all disc / combat ability timers greyed out for a 5 – 10 minutes or limited movement and attack speed while ‘resting’, would be appreciated.</LI></UL>
<OL></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></SPAN></OL>
<P><BR><STRONG>8. Savage Spirit AA <FONT color=#ff0000>NEW</FONT></STRONG></P>
<UL>
<LI>Some of the AA disciplines are falling short of the expectations, especially Savage Spirit. The randomish nature and the fact that it doesn't stack with Veterans Wrath oftentimes cause the disc to produce only medicore results and not 'massive damage' as indicated in the AA description. We'd like this skill reviewed to show much more reliable and 'massive' results, i.e. a shorter duration disc with some garuanteed big blows.</LI></UL>
<P><STRONG>9. Desperation AA&nbsp; <FONT color=#ff0000>NEW</FONT></STRONG></P>
<UL>
<LI>Desperation is currently one of the 'Hate it or love it' AAs as the concept of the skill is very well recieved, but the actual performance is in most cases lacking. The skill is very hard and very very risky to use effectively and the reward seems to be too low for that.<BR></LI></UL></DIV>
								<p><div style="width: 100%; height: 120; overflow: hidden;">
								
							*************************************************<br>Ashlanne Barefoot<br>Community Relations Coordinator<br>Norrath, where I kick off my shoes and run in bare feet.<br><b><a href="http://stationforums.station.sony.com/communitysoe/ "><font color="red">Check out the Station Forums!</font></a>
							</div>
								
		</td></tr>
